Beta Phase said it hasagreed to sell its shape-memory eyeglass frame manufacturingtechnology and equipment to privately-held Universal Optical.    The company said Universal Optical will also purchase theexisting Beta Phase inventory of raw materials, its work inprogress and its manufacturing equipment and tooling.    Under the pact, Beta Phase will receive a 20 pct share ofCVI/Beta Ventures, a joint venture owned by Beta Group andCooperVision Inc &lt;EYE>, which markets worldwide shape memoryeyeglass frames. The venture will then be owned 54 pct by BetaGroup, 26 pct by Coopervision and 20 pct by Beta Phase. Reuter&#3;